<P><H1 align=center>VERIFICATION DETAIL – DC031</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields in shown red 
are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT></P>
<P>This screen is used to register that the applicant’s identification has been 
checked and verified. The screen is divided into two sections, (Personal 
identification and Residency identification).</P>
<P><H3>Personal Identification: </H3>select the appropriate 
form of identification from the drop-down list. Eg. birth certificate, driving 
licence, passport. Then enter the reference number in the field on the right 
hand side of the screen
<P></P>
<P><H3>Residency Identification: </H3>select the appropriate 
form of identification from the drop-down list. Eg. utility bill, council tax 
demand, credit card statement. Then enter the reference number in the field on 
the right hand side of the screen
<P></P>
<P><STRONG>Note: </STRONG>if ‘Other’ is selected from either list, a field will appear under 
‘Other Type’ to specify the type of document</P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>click on ‘OK’ to return to&nbsp;the previous 
screen.

